            <p><strong>The Truth:</strong>
          All of the land and buildings that comprise the airport will continue to be owned with the Government of Bermuda. Aecon will not hold any ownership of the property or facilities. The title to the airport remains with the Bermuda Government. This is simply a partnership between a public enterprise and a private enterprise, similar to the public-private partnership which was used to build to our new hospital. The opposition did not object to that agreement. In fact, they helped arrange it.
